{"attack":true,"case":"The proposal violates std-crit-design clause (2) and the honesty/measurability clause via forbidden case 3. The case 'Observed FP-removal rate on correct-majority questions exceeds 50% of observed TP-removal rate while harness still beats SC' is not a concrete, measurable outcome refuting the proposal as written: the proposal's own mechanism conditions net benefit on 'FP removal rate < TP removal rate scaled by majority-margin,' a scaling that varies with the realized majority-margin distribution, not a flat 50% constant. More importantly, 'correct-majority questions' requires the held-out answer key to classify which questions had a correct majority, but the harness scores one shared candidate pool per question and the answer key is held out from every model call; determining the TP/FP removal split per question-category at runtime conflates the held-out key into the filtering layer's operating statistics, breaking the shared-pool/held-out design. The case is therefore not cleanly measurable by rerunning the repository's validation harness without leaking the answer key into the filtering evaluation. Forbidden cases 1 and 2 are well-formed, but case 3 is a non-refuting, non-measurable artifact.","counterexample":null}